<h3>How do I display a man page source file? (i.e. one whose filename
ends in a number, like tcpdump.8).</h3>
d380 2
a381 2
This is found throughout the src tree. The man pages are found in the
tree unformatted, and many times through the use of
d383 1
a383 1
pages simply :
d387 1
a387 1
<strong># nroff -mandoc &lt;file&gt; | more</strong>
d402 1
a402 1
<strong># man &lt;command&gt; | col -b</strong>
d410 2
a411 2
Note that <tt>[man_src_file]</tt> must be the man page source file (probably a
file that ends in a number; e.g., <tt>tcpdump.8</tt>). The PostScript versions of
d415 1
a415 1
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=groff&amp;sektion=1">groff(1)</a>
d421 40
a460 1
<strong># groff -mandoc -Tps [man_src_file] &gt; outfile.ps</strong>
d464 48
d700 1
