<p>
If you do not have
access to a PostScript printer or display, you may also format the
documents for reading on a terminal display, using <tt>"make paper.txt"</tt>
instead of <tt>"make"</tt>. This will produce an ASCII text document called
<tt>"paper.txt"</tt>, suitable for viewing with a pager such as
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=less&amp;sektion=1">less(1)</a>.
However, this will only work within specific sections of a distribution
directory.
